NZBGet is a binary downloader, which downloads files from Usenet
based on information given in nzb-files. NZBGet is written in C++
and is known for its extraordinary performance and efficiency.

You'll need to create a nzbget user in order to run with the provided init
script:

# useradd -r -d /var/lib/nzbget nzbget

You'll also need to add the following to /etc/rc.d/rc.local

if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.nzbget ]; then
    /etc/rc.d/rc./nzbget start
fi

And the following to /etc/rc.d/rc.local_shutdown

if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.nzbget ]; then
    /etc/rc.d/rc./nzbget stop
fi
